 Maven dependency or Docker service is needed: vertx-web-client is normally used as an async HTTP client over Vert.x/Netty and the resolved artifact brings its required Vert.x and Netty runtime dependencies. However, native execution on JDK 25 with Vert.x 5.0.1 / Netty 4.2.2.Final concretely needs the Netty unsafe-access runtime properties; without them the existing coverage fails with Netty allocator NPEs and closed/reset HTTP streams.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime tests on JDK 25/current-defaults, set runtime system properties `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`. Generated tests can use an in-process Vert.x `HttpServer` on localhost for meaningful coverage; no external HTTP service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The unsafe-access property is tied to JDK 25 / Netty 4.2.x behavior and should be verified by local Gradle/native-image runs.\",\n    \"Tests that exercise streaming or multipart uploads are likely to fail in native mode without these runtime properties.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_047ac93cca27660f016a416d55b1fc8194a50e590a977b5123\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1390, "output": 673, "cacheRead": 47616, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49679, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782672716932, "responseId": "resp_047ac93cca27660f016a416d4d60f881948ae5b501bf199c7f"}}
